<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{5}{y}={41}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{7}{y}={45}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -9. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{9}}{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{9}}}{{2}}{\left({2}{x}+{5}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{9}}}{{2}}{\left({41}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({9}\right)}{x}+-{22.5}{y}=-{184.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{7}{y}={45}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{15.5}{y}=-{139.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{139.5}}{{-{{15.5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{5}{\left({9}\right)}={41}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{\left({45}\right)}={41}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={41}-{\left({45}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}=-{4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{4}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

